 |CKBDarkwind Remort
|WKO~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 |YKORemort is Darkwind's late-game rebirth loop. When you reach
 level 250, you may choose to remort: your character returns to
 level 1 and climbs again, carrying a permanent remort level that
 grows by one with every rebirth.

 Remorting is always optional. You can stay at level 250 forever
 and never remort.

 |MKBWhat you give up each remort:
  |YKO- Your level (back to 1) and any unspent experience
  - Your base stats (back to 1, rebuilt with stat raises)
  - Your guild memberships (you leave all guilds)

 |MKBWhat you keep, always:
  |YKO- Your name, history, and account progress
  - Your gold, bank balance, boats, and property
  - Your inventory
  - Your remort level, boon points, and every boon you have chosen

 |MKBWhat you gain:
  |YKO- One |YKBboon point |YKOper remort level, spent on permanent bonuses
    that persist through every future life (see |YKBhelp boons|YKO)
  - Automatic leveling: remort players advance the moment they
    have enough experience, with no guild-hall visit
  - 6 stat raises per level (spend with |YKBadvance |YKOat a guild hall;
    stats are capped at 3 x your level)
  - A remort tag (R1, R2, ...) on the who list

 |MKBThe cost:
  |YKORemort use a variation of the normal level experience curve. Each
  remort level adds 10% to that cost. A soul that has lived many
  lives climbs more slowly, but carries far more power with it.

 |MKBCommands:
  |YKB remort          |YKOShow your remort status and eligibility
  |YKB remort boons    |YKOList the permanent bonuses you can choose
  |YKB remort choose   |YKOSpend a boon point
  |YKB remort confirm  |YKORemort (only at level 250, asked only once)
  |YKB marks           |YKOShow the boons marked on your soul

 |YKOSee also: |YKBhelp boons|YKO, |YKBhelp leveling|YKO.
